I whimped out when I bought my relays and didn't bother looking for OG
relays. Instead, I went to my local NAPA and got their parts book for
relays. I then went through all the relays with the foreign pin designation
required and then narrowed it down to 14 part numbers that all had mounting
tabs. Out of that list I picked the one they had the most of on the shelf
which turned out to be an air conditioning control relay for a Cadillac. Not
very scientific, but hey, I have a whole list of substitution parts if need
be.

